 aspirations are realized. Together, the three peethas-the Maya Devi Temple, the Chandi Devi Temple, and this particular Manasa Temple-are found in Haridwar. It is of great religious significance not only because it is a temple but also because Haridwar is thought to be among the four locations where droplets of elixir mistakenly dropped while being transported by Lord Vishnu's chariot, Garuda. It's possible that this is the reason why this magnificent temple in northern India has some of the most visitors. Another feature that contributes to the temple's beauty and draws visitors from all over the nation is the ropeways that ascend to it. 4. Shantikunj A well-known ashram in the world, Shantikunj has become known as the center of moral renewal. It is the All World Gayatri Pariwar (AWGP) headquarters, and it is situated in Haridwar. The AWGP has millions of adherents and is attended by notable figures like the Dalai Lama, who is morally regarded, and other spiritual authorities like Murari Bapu. This pilgrimage location, a school for social and spiritual awakening, has led a lot of lives down the correct path and provided them with enduring satisfaction. It promotes national unity and the awakening of people's moral, spiritual, and religious values. This ashram offers spiritual guidance and helps people become even more enlightened. It is now a perfect location where the general public receives training based on divine spiritual teachings. It strives to bring back Rishi's heritage. The primary mission is to help humanity become more divine. Traditional cultural settings, including the Yagya shala, Akhand Deep, and temples like Gayatri Mata Temple and Devatma Himalaya Temple, can be found at the Shantikunj Ashram. Along with an Exhibition of Divine Culture, it also has temples dedicated to ancient Rishis. 5. Patanjali Yog Peeth In Haridwar, Uttarakhand, there is a yoga and ayurvedic research center called Patanjali Yogpeeth. It is also highly recognized for being one