tions. By eradicating illnesses without the need for allopathic medicine and its adverse effects, it seeks to bring about world peace, healthy life, and satisfaction. Yoga treatment and therapy serve as the key tool for achieving this. This Yogpeeth is frequented by those seeking Ayurvedic care and drugs. It's interesting to note that in addition to Ayurvedic therapies, there are divisions for study and research-focused laboratories, as well as facilities for a canteen, residential housing, and an ATM for use. This Yogapeeth institution has two campuses, the Patanjali Yogapeeth I and the Patanjali Yogapeeth II. Both of these divisions work together to carry out social welfare initiatives in the medical fields, schooling, and other social, cultural, and economic activities. The institute offers regular yoga sessions and training in a number of different yoga techniques. It also has a hospital where travelers from all around the world can receive ayurvedic care. It's because a production facility for ayurvedic medicines is located here. There is a lodging option available for guests who want to stay in this location. 6. Bara Bazar Bara Bazar is one of the tourist destinations in Haridwar for people who want to enjoy shopping and purchasing the items that Haridwar is well known for. This bustling Bazar is the city's major shopping destination. This crowded alley market is stocked with religious souvenirs and other accessories for both domestic and international visitors who are flocking in large numbers. Here, one may find everything from Rudraksha seeds to herbal goods and medications to digestive supplements like Churans to artisan goods and jewelry. It is also a fantastic area to shop for wooden goods, and for those who enjoy sweets, there are many different kinds of sweets available in sweet stores. The regional specialty created from milk, "Pedas," deserves special note. The delectable Peda that is sold here in great quantities can be consumed and taken home. 7. P